The Best Director award at the 93rd Academy Awards held in 2021 was won by Chloé Zhao for her work on the film "Nomadland". Chloé Zhao made history as the first woman of color to win the Best Director Oscar. "Nomadland" also won several other awards at the 2021 ceremony, including Best Picture, Best Actress for Frances McDormand, and Best Adapted Screenplay for Chloé Zhao.